        <div type="recipe">
        <p> Cut the Rind of China Oranges in long Chips, but very thin, and with none of the White; boil them in Water ’ till they are very tender; then drain them, and put them into a very thick cold Syrup of clarify ’ d Sugar; let them lye a Day or two; then scald them, and when they are cold lay them to dry on Earthen Plates in a Stove. Sevil Oranges will do the same Way, if you like them with a little Sugar, and very bitter. </p>
